text: Justika Sjarifuddin Baharsjah (born 7 May 1937) is an Indonesian activist and politician. She was born in Cianjur, West Java. She was Minister of Agriculture from March to May 1998. She also was Minister of Social Affairs from 1998 to 1999. She was married to Sjarifuddin Baharsjah. ==References== Category:1937 births Category:Living people Category:Indonesian politicians Category:Indonesian activists
